name: Energy Income Fund
longDescription: The Fund's investment objectives are to provide its unitholders with a stable stream of monthly distributions and to preserve and potentially enhance the Net Asset Value (NAV) of the Fund. The Fund is permitted to invest in any publicly listed securities in the United States. For investments in other geographies, the Fund allocates its assets across several asset classes without specific reference to any issuer or security. These classes include oil and gas securities, energy securities, other resource securities, as well as cash and short-term investments. The Manager, guided by the Investment Manager, determines the appropriate asset class for each portfolio security, and this determination is final.
